{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01AMmyqf19PuT8i7zruaxGCW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nThe test plan above identifies the **minimum infrastructure needed** to catch real failures for each behavior:\n\n- **Unit level** (Behaviors 3, 6): Pure logic with no external dependencies—sorting and semver comparison.\n- **Integration level** (Behaviors 1, 2, 4, 7): Multi-component interactions requiring realistic data (manifest files, version constraints) or well-designed mocks that validate constraints.\n- **System level** (Behavior 5): Real git operations and API calls needed to verify PR creation on an actual repository.\n\n**Key takeaway**: Mocking is insufficient for behaviors 1, 2, 4, and 5 because mocks can hide failures in:\n- Transitive dependency resolution (would need accurate emulation)\n- Version range matching (could return arbitrary results)\n- Manifest format preservation (could silently corrupt formatting)\n- PR creation mechanics (would need real git/API behavior)\n\nFor Behavior 7, the integration between breaking change detection → PR skip → output flag is where subtle bugs hide—individual Unit tests of each component would pass while the integration fails."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5558,"cache_read_input_tokens":46839,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5558},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abedc1ba-a17e-4146-856f-f8c5d2ad26b5","uuid":"7913594d-732e-48f1-8f75-c1020e5ed147"}
